Here’s to 2022 , anyone else kinda excited for 2023?? I know I am. 
-
I’ve learned so much this year. 
-
Patience, boundaries, and finally really discovering my own self worth.

Living in AUSTIN alone isn’t easy so working hard to make sure I can live alone and happy is important. Now I’m getting to the point I feel like I’ve plateaued and ready to really branch out. I’ve said before I wanted to get back to posting and being more social and well life/ bad relationship hit me. Now processing and growing through that I’m ready to take things on for myself again. Realizing that I shouldn’t hold myself back for others and or doubt in myself.. if I failed at least I tried and I can do better next time. Here’s to a new year, new me 🤙 Have a strong feeling 2023 is going to be the best yet.

Let me know what you think.

Happy 2023 ✨

I hope you are starting this year off right. Whatever it is, big or small do something for you. You can always improve, learn or accomplish new goals. 
-
This year I’m going focus on me and my worth. I’ve seen me struggle with relationships and self doubt far to long and I feel it’s something I really owe myself. 
-
This last year thought me how strong I have been my entire life and kinda how I’ve been not really ever showing myself the love I need. 
-
I hope you can reflect on your year and decide now what you want to change, what you need to stop doing or leave behind for YOU. Be happy, do what makes your heart smile and fall inlove with yourself ❤️ 
-
Happy new year babes, make it the best yet.

Self Love is something I’ve really struggled with my entire life. 
-
This year I really am focusing on mental health and just being a better person to myself. My self worth also affects the people around me in different ways. I’m insecure and sometimes still get intrusive thoughts but I have to remind myself how far I’ve came. 
-
I really hope anyone struggling knows that nothing is forever and you just have to try a little everyday. You’ll look back and see what all you’ve accomplished. Put that love into yourself, allow yourself to be happy or at least try. You are worth it.

I’m done letting my past consume me. I’m done hiding my abuse because I’m scared. I don’t care who judges me I don’t care who you get think you are what you aren’t I’m doing this for me and to help other people going through the same thing.. you are mean, you are hateful and full of lies.

You never helped me, you never donated, you did not ever take me to my dr I wasn’t even living in ga I was in Tennessee when I started my transition. We always had child services come, we never had a real home till Andrew and you even ruined him. 
Watching those videos makes me sick. This is why I have been alone and no I haven’t been the best person but I’ve done best with what I could.. and for the drugs I am stoner and we BOTH smoked weed. You kicked me out for your new man and because I was going to try to help the kids go to their dads so I could leave again and ALL of us get away from you. The neighbors didn’t kick me out , literally doesn’t even make sense. They didn’t even like you because you started going crazy and trying to fight them! You deserve to everything you are getting. You hurt and betray/ use every single person around you. You are why I struggle every day deciding if I’m worth living or not.. but also you are why I am so strong and different. When I told you I was trans you said I just didn’t want to be a girl because I was raped and touched. You lied about dad, you lied about me and now created some fantasy life for you to mold I to because you are wicked human.

Cheers to getting sober.. yesterday I blacked out and my trama again came out. Cause me to lose someone that’s done nothing but make me feel loved, seen and cared for. I have a hard time with loving myself and in turn reflects the belief anyone else would. 
-
That being said I lost a love that was true and probably will never get the chance to have again. 
-
I suffer with my bad thoughts a lot and right now I’m on the edge, honestly.. I’m so tired of the feelings I have and constant doubt. I want to get better and when I know I am it’s like I sabotage myself! I want to be happy, I want to love and be loved, I don’t want to keep feeling alone and unlovable . 
-
Thank you for the people who reached out I’m sorry if I triggered anyone. I’m just not okay and now losing someone I cared so much for simply because my mental sucks.. 
-
I will get better I know I will, I have to remember where I’ve came from and gotten through. My story isn’t over of I don’t want it to be. I have to let go and allow myself happiness and light. I need to stop staying in the dark and hurting my own person. I don’t want to be alone anymore.. I don’t want to be sad and angry or need to drink to try to numb my feelings. 
-
I have a problem and I have to fix it before one day I choose something more permanent like my dad. I say all the time I want to be with him but I know I belong here and to be happy. 
-
My heart is heavy asf rn so if I don’t have the mental to reach out know I’m thankful . I’m sorry..

Little update: I’ve been really not feeling like myself or motivated. A few of you know a couple months ago I quit my job found another one with better pay and less labor on my body. “Wasn’t able to gym” “caused dysphoria” Well I took a nap cause I hadn’t been sleeping well, ended up putting my alarm for am not pm and didn’t wake up. Obviously resulted in me being let go. So I been looking, finally got a job at the airport. Been waiting about a month now for everything to process and should have my background check this week. With my not working I’ve been doing o.f. And whatever on the side to get money for bills, ect. 
Today I was feeling really low and needed to get outside, change my vibe and it did help. 
-
Just know if you are struggling rn whatever it is you aren’t the only one and we need to support and lift each other up. Be there for each other and most importantly show up for yourself, we got this

Sooo little “T” for ya.. first shot in about two months. Needless to say I’m ready to feel like myself again. It’s been a crazy rocky couple months with change and figuring out things. I let my mental and wellbeing slip and not be prioritized first. Let me tell you that’s probably the worst thing to do when you’re already low. The more care you give to yourself, the love and discipline will come back. You don’t love or care for you, it’ll come back as well. You have to choose to fight, choose to love you and continue to strive for better. Not every day, week nor month will be ideal maybe. At least you can look back and see the strides you took and the accomplishments you achieved. Sending you love and light and don’t forget to take care of yourself. 🩵🩷
